-- slice 5b: a multi-arm match on a TUPLE.  The decision-tree lowering discriminates
-- the tuple with an HTuple n switch head (one branch, since every arm is a 2-tuple),
-- then descends into the element columns with nested int-literal switches.  The
-- emitter must treat HTuple like a constructor test against hashName "$tuple"
-- (arity n) — the same tag tuple construction stamps.
classify p = match p
  (0, y) => y
  (x, 0) => x
  (x, y) => x + y

main = classify (0, 5) + classify (3, 0) + classify (2, 4)
